Answer.ValidTrueComment:
The system does not properly disable accounts after 35 days of inactivity.
Remediation: 1. Set system default: useradd -D -f 35 2. Verify /etc/default/useradd shows INACTIVE=35 3. Set for existing accounts: chage -I 35 USERNAME (for each user) 4. Verify per-user settings: chage -l USERNAME (check "Password inactive") 5. For all users: awk -F: '{print $1}' /etc/passwd | xargs -I{} chage -I 35 {}
Contact the system administrator to configure account inactivity lockout per DoD 35-day requirement.
